# Design System Usage

All UI work MUST use the design system at `@/ui`. Never use raw HTML elements or inline styles for things the design system already provides.

## Import

```tsx
import { Button, TextInput, Typography, DESIGN_SYSTEM_COLORS, DESIGN_SYSTEM_SPACING } from '@/ui'
```

## Components Available

- **Button** тАФ variants: `primary | secondary | outline | ghost`, sizes: `sm | md | lg`, props: `loading`, `disabled`, `fullWidth`
- **TextInput** тАФ props: `label`, `error`, `inputSize` (`sm | md | lg`), `disabled`, `fullWidth`
- **Typography** тАФ variants: `h1 | h2 | h3 | h4 | body | caption | overline`, props: `weight`, `align`, `color`

## Styling Rules

- Use **Tailwind utility classes** for layout, spacing, and responsiveness тАФ never inline `style={{}}` for these
- Use design tokens from `@/ui/theme.css` via Tailwind classes: `bg-primary-500`, `text-neutral-700`, `p-md`, `rounded-lg`, etc.
- Responsive breakpoints: mobile-first тЖТ `md:` (tablet 768px) тЖТ `lg:` (desktop 1024px)
- Animations: use `framer-motion` (`motion.*` elements) for entrance/interaction тАФ keep them subtle

## Examples

```tsx
// тЭМ BAD тАФ raw elements, inline styles
<button style={{ padding: '8px 16px', background: 'blue', color: 'white' }}>Save</button>
<input style={{ border: '1px solid gray' }} />
<h1 style={{ fontSize: '2rem' }}>Title</h1>

// тЬЕ GOOD тАФ design system components + Tailwind layout
<Button variant="primary" size="md">Save</Button>
<TextInput label="Email" placeholder="you@example.com" fullWidth />
<Typography variant="h1">Title</Typography>
```

## Extending the Design System

When a new reusable component is needed:
1. Create it in `src/ui/components/`
2. Export it from `src/ui/components/index.ts`
3. Use design tokens from `theme.css` тАФ do not hardcode colors or spacing
4. Add framer-motion subtle entrance animation
5. Support all 3 breakpoints (mobile, tablet, desktop)
